snippet.title: [NEU Blockchain] Step Into the Blockchain Industry
snippet.description:
Blockchains are known for their role in cryptocurrency systems for maintaining a secure and decentralized record of transactions. The global blockchain market has grown tremendously in recent years and is expected to increase by billions over the next few years.



Contributing to this high market growth rate include increasing venture capital fundings, investment in technology, use of blockchain solutions in banking and cybersecurity, high adoption of blockchain solutions for payment, smart contracts, and digital identities.


In this panel discussion and blockchain event hosted in collaboration with Northeastern University’s Blockchain Organization, learn about how to step into this rapidly growing industry.


Hear about working in this unique space from Professor Felipe Cortes, Sydney Rice, S’18, and Toju Ometoruwa, DMSB’16.


Get hands-on with the team and researchers in the NEU Blockchain Organization with the opportunity to set up your digital wallet, and meet others in the community!

This video is the property of NEU Blockchain and is to be used for educational and informational purposes only. Any illegal reproduction of this content will result in immediate legal action.

snippet.title: [NEU Blockchain] Intro to Coin Metrics
snippet.description:
CEO Tim Rice and the Research team from Coin Metrics join Northeastern Blockchain to discuss the analytics and findings behind cryptocurrencies.

Coin Metrics is the leading provider of transparent and actionable crypto asset market and network data, delivering mature data across multiple formats to various industry stakeholders including financial enterprises, crypto funds, media and research outlets, and third-party data and application providers. Coin Metrics’ data empowers its clients and the public to better understand, value, use, and ultimately steward public crypto networks.
